<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-78-0776 </DOCNO><TEXT>This paper is to discuss the alternate methods of overpressure protection.In considering methods of overpressure protection, three primary criteriacan be considered. These are: a. CONTINUITY - Does the system continueto be supplied with gas? 2. CONTAINMENT - Is gas released to the atmosphereor is it contained within the gas piping system? 3. NOTIFICATION - Isthere adequate awareness by the gas system operator that the backup overpressuredevice is in operation? There are three basic methods of overpressureprotection. These are: Automatic shut-off, Pressure relief, and Monitoring.Using the evaluation criteria for each of these reveals the following.</TEXT></DOC>